import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='age', bins=10)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of ages in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.boxplot(data=data, y='height')
    median_height = data['height'].median()
    plt.axhline(y=median_height, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Median Height: {median_height:.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the average height of people in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
